  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Network Engineer (12-month Contract)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p>We are seeking a <strong>Network Engineer</strong> to support the implementation, maintenance, and day-to-day operations of enterprise network and security infrastructure. This role involves close collaboration with internal teams and customers to ensure reliable, secure, and compliant network environments.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Support the implementation, operation, and maintenance of network infrastructure, including firewalls, switches, and routers</li><li>Assist with configuration, monitoring, and troubleshooting of network connectivity and security-related issues</li><li>Perform firewall rule updates, clean-up, and basic hardening in accordance with established guidelines</li><li>Support network changes, upgrades, and migrations, ensuring proper documentation and change records</li><li>Assist with incident resolution, log review, and routine operational security checks</li><li>Provide operational support for LAN/WAN environments and endpoint connectivity</li><li>Prepare implementation checklists and support pre-deployment and post-deployment activities</li><li>Work closely with team members to ensure adherence to internal policies and customer requirements</li><li>Maintain network diagrams, configurations, and technical documentation</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p><strong>Qualifications & Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Degree or diploma in Information Technology, Computer Networks, or a related field</li><li>Hands-on experience in network or IT infrastructure support roles</li><li>Experience supporting firewall and switching environments in enterprise settings</li><li>Familiarity with routing, switching, and fundamental network security concepts</li><li>Experience working in support, implementation, or operations teams</li></ul><p><strong>Technical Skills</strong></p><ul><li>Basic configuration and support of firewalls (e.g. Palo Alto, Fortinet, Check Point, or equivalent)</li><li>Good understanding of TCP/IP, VLANs, routing, switching, and the OSI model</li><li>Ability to troubleshoot network and connectivity issues effectively</li><li>Exposure to compliance or audit support is an advantage</li><li>Familiarity with standard networking tools and documentation practices</li></ul>",
